; ESH-0119 regression: a stack-overflow from deep non-tail recursion must be a
; CLEAN, diagnosable failure — the runtime prints an "[Eshkol] fatal signal"
; stack-overflow diagnostic and exits nonzero — NOT a silent SIGILL (rc132 with
; no output).
;
; This program is EXPECTED to crash. The harness that runs it
; (scripts/run_stack_overflow_diagnostic.sh) asserts:
;   (1) exit code is nonzero, AND
;   (2) stderr contains the fatal-signal / stack-overflow diagnostic.
;
; Depth 5,000,000 is far past every measured overflow ceiling
; (see docs/reports/RECURSION_DEPTH_REPORT.md: non_tail safe ~200k) on default stacks, so it
; reliably exhausts the native stack on both the JIT (-r) and AOT lanes.
(define (down n)
  (if (= n 0) 0 (+ 1 (down (- n 1)))))

(display "entering deep non-tail recursion\n")
(display (down 5000000))
(newline)
